"{\"uid\": \"standard.co.uk-news-world-eiffel-tower-climber-paris-olympics-2024-closing-ceremony-b1175899.html\", \"text\": \"To use the search feature, we need your consent to load Google Custom Search, which may use cookies or similar technologies. Please click 'Allow and Continue' below to enable search. See our privacy policy for more information.  News|World  French authorities have evacuated the area around theEiffel Towerafter a man was seen climbing the world-famous landmark hours before theOlympicsclosing ceremony.  Barclays plans to relocate European base from Dublin to Paris  Hottest hotel openings for 2026  London named as 'the best food city in the world'  Make 2026 the year of working smarter  The shirtless man was seen scaling the 1,083ft (330m)Paristourist attraction on Sunday afternoon.  It was unclear where he began his ascent, but he was spotted just above the Olympic rings adorning the second section of the monument, beyond the first viewing deck.  Police escorted visitors away from the area at around 3pm. Some who were briefly locked on the second floor were allowed to leave around 30 minutes later.  The closing ceremony is set to begin at the Stade de France in the Saint-Denis area,well away from the Tower, at around 9pm.  More than 30,000 police officers have been deployed around Paris and beyond to watch over the last Olympic events and Sunday's closing ceremony.  France's interior minister, Gerald Darmanin, said about 3,000 police officers will be mobilised around the Stade de France, and 20,000 police troops and other security personnel in Paris and the Saint-Denis area will be mobilised late into Sunday night to ensure safety on the last day of the Games.  This year's Olympics marked the third time Paris has hosted the modern Games in its history.  MORE ABOUT  Have your say...  1  Crime  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line train after youths told to stop vaping by middle-aged passenger  Fight breaks out on Elizabeth line after youths told to stop vaping  2  Football  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup, confirmed team news, injury latest for Premier League today  Liverpool XI vs Brighton: Starting lineup and confirmed team news  3  UK  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning over Donald Trump's Iran war  Flights alert: UK issues global travel disruption warning on Iran war  4  Lifestyle  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  Horoscope today: Your daily guide for Saturday, March 21, 2026  5  Football  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news, predicted lineup, injury latest for Carabao Cup final  Arsenal XI vs Man City: Confirmed team news and predicted lineup\"}"